reviewerName: Don't tread on me "Defending the Conservative...
reviewText: I would have to say that I still like Santa Baby 1 better than 2.  However, this was a good Christmas movie worth adding to my collection.  The story is funny, and most of the original cast is back.  For the most part, the cast changes are good ones.  I can't really think of any that made me think the change runied the movie.  Most of the original elves are back as well.Unlike some of the other movies from ABC "Family" that have come out at Christmas, such as Holiday in Handcuffs, this movie is actually enjoyable and okay for the entire family.  ABC did not try to forward their liberal / statist agenda with this movie.  It is a just a good Christmas movie for a change.
Title: Santa Baby 2

Title: Santa Baby 2

reviewText: In Santa Baby 2: Christmas Maybe Jenny McCarthy is back as Mary Class.  Mary is the daughter of Santa Claus (Paul Sorvino) who has to head back to the North Pole to help her dad run the toy  shop. Mary and her boyfriend, Luke (Dean McDermott) comes back home to the North Pole when they grew-up.  One reason Mary has to return to the North Pole is Santa is dealing with a late-life crisis.  Santa is ready to retire, he is tired of the responsiblities of being Santa.  Santa is ready to pass the job down to Mary.  But Mary has completion for the Santa job.  A young woman named Teri (Kelly Stables) who is the post office carrier and the assistant for Santa wants to take Mary down for the job.  Watch this movie to see what happens to these characters. Hint: there is surprise about Teri!  Who will deliver the presents to the children? Will it Mary, Santa, or Teri?
summary: Entertaining! Perfect Movie for this Time of Year!

Title: Santa Baby 2

reviewText: I enjoyed the first installment more, but then that is the norm, right? Jenny McCarthy does a great job as Santa Claus' daughter and Dean McDermott does a great job as her husband. I love the atmosphere portrayed in the "north pole", with the decorations and the elves and all of the activity. Santa wants to travel with his newly formed band, he's tired, so his daughter, a successful business woman, tries to incorporate new ideas which end up in disaster. Not to worry though, everything always works out at Christmas. I watch both Santa Baby and Santa Baby 2 every year.
Title: Santa Baby 2
